Appendix 3  9
OUTLINE OF TERMS OF REFERENCE FOR CONSULTANTS 

A.  Trade Economist (international, 12 person-months) 
1.  The  consultant  will  have  a  postgraduate-level  background  in  international  trade, 
macroeconomics, or public policy, with in-depth expertise in international trade policies, regional 
economic cooperation, trade negotiations; and substantial knowledge of current developments 
in economic integration in the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN). The consultant 
will  

(i)  assist in preparing the work plan for the Office of Regional Economic Integration 
(OREI) and the Bureau of Economic Integration and Finance (BEIF);  
(ii)  in consultation with BEIF and OREI, identify special issues that require further in-
depth study; 
(iii)  prepare (or assist in preparing) policy briefs on topics identified by the ASEAN 
Secretariat (ASEC) and agreed to by the Asian Development Bank  (ADB) in 
advance; 
(iv)  coordinate implementation of the ASEAN Economic Community (AEC) with other 
ASEAN bodies; 
(v)  prepare regular status reports on AEC implementation; 
(vi)  provide in-house capacity development support as needed and appropriate;  
(vii)  assist  in  developing  the  database  system  for  ASEC,  including  key 
macroeconomic indicators and an interactive statistical tool that can be accessed 
on the ASEAN website; 
(viii)  provide  inputs  for  key  speeches  of  the  ASEAN  Secretary-General  and  ADB 
President on issues related to ASEAN economic integration; 
(ix)  prepare terms of reference for international consultants as needed; and 
(x)  undertake other tasks as required by ASEC and OREI. 

B.  Macroeconomist (international, 12 person-months) 
2.  The consultant will have a postgraduate-level background in macroeconomics with in-
depth expertise in regional macroeconomic surveillance and substantial knowledge of current 
developments in ASEAN economic integration. The consultant will  

(i)  assist in preparing the work plan for OREI and BEIF;  
(ii)  in consultation with BEIF and OREI, identify special issues that require further in-
depth study; 
(iii)  prepare (or assist in preparing) policy briefs on topics identified by ASEC and 
agreed to by ADB in advance; 
(iv)  coordinate with ASEAN Finance Ministers (AFMs) and other concerned ASEAN 
officials; 
(v)  provide in-house capacity development support as needed and appropriate;  
(vi)  assist  in  developing  the  database  system  for  ASEC,  including  key 
macroeconomic indicators and an interactive statistical tool that can be accessed 
on the ASEAN website; 
(vii)  provide  inputs  for  key  speeches  of  the  ASEAN  Secretary-General  and  ADB 
President on issues related to ASEAN economic integration; 
(viii)  prepare terms of reference for international consultants as needed; and 
(ix)  undertake other tasks as required by ASEC and OREI.
